For those interested in the Kerberos 5 ticket-retrieving feature, it is now 
available for testing.  Many thanks to Mark Earnest at Penn State for 
writing this part of IISCosign!

<http://www.umich.edu/~umweb/software/cosign/download.html>

This is a dll only.  You will probably want to run the 1.1.1 installer 
before using 1.2.0 beta.

Add at least the following line to your cosign.dll.config file:

<GetKerberosTickets>FALSE</GetKerberosTickets>

If you want this set to TRUE you'll need:

<GetKerberosTickets>TRUE</GetKerberosTickets>
<KerberosTicketsPath>c:\Kerb5tkts</KerberosTickets>

With the TRUE setting you'll have a new server variable, HTTP_KRB5CCNAME. 
The value is set to FILE:[KerberosTicketsPath]\[TicketFile].  Please report 
any problems, concerns, or successes to cosign@umich.edu.

--Jarod Malestein
--University of Michigan
h

