Subject: Cosign 2.0.0b1 Released
Date: Thu, 4 May 2006 12:18:00 -0400
X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.749.3)

The Cosign Team is pleased to announce the availability of the first  
BETA release Cosign 2.0!

Cosign 2.0.0b1 [ MD5 22076feda618edb31a3aeecb9537081c ]

Changes in this release include a new version of the cosign protocol,  
the addition of Multifactor authentication, and the new external  
authenticator API for the CGI. A full detail of changes is available at
http://www.umich.edu/~umweb/software/cosign/changelog.txt

Things we have yet to test in depth:

1) replication with multiple factors/the v2 protocol
2) anything under any sort of load
3) extensive compatibility tests**
4) building with no legacy factors ( no krb and no friend ) and using  
only an external authenticator
5) upgrading a production server, or any server with existing logged  
in users

This new release is up for download at http://www.umich.edu/~umweb/ 
software/cosign/download.html

We're going to keep testing it here at Michigan and plan to be  
rolling it out within the next month. Feedback is encouraged and  
welcomed as always.

-Johanna and the Core Cosign Development Team

**it should all just work, and we've tried several old/new combos  
upgraded server and older filters, upgraded filters and old server,  
upgraded server and older cgi... but nothing extensive. the 2.0 CGI  
requires a 2.0 cosignd.

