MIME-Version: 1.0
To: cosign-announce@umich.edu
Subject: IISCosign 2.0.0 beta filter available
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1; format=flowed
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit


A beta of the cosign filter for IIS, version 2.0.0, is now available.

http://www.umich.edu/~umweb/software/cosign/download.html
MD5 52812510d864f23db92508491ccedb8a


Changes:
+ Multi-factor support
+ SiteEntry config option added
+ PostErrorRedirect config option added
+ CheckIPAddress options are now never, intial, or always
+ Apache-style protected/unprotected/protected configuration.  For 
example, you can have "/subdir" protected and then set 
"/subdir/notimportant" to unprotected.
+ Updated logging messages.

To use multi-factor, you need a 2.0.0+ Cosign login server.  IISCosign 
2.0.0 is backwards compatible with earlier versions of cosign.

There are some significant changes to the cosign.dll.config file.   
Please see the included sample config file!

Please send any questions or comments to cosign@umich.edu.

--Jarod


